.TH "devm_pinctrl_register_and_init" 9 "devm_pinctrl_register_and_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_pinctrl_register_and_init \- Resource managed pinctrl register and init
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" devm_pinctrl_register_and_init
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct pinctrl_desc *pctldesc "  ","
.BI "void *driver_data "  ","
.BI "struct pinctrl_dev **pctldev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
parent device for this pin controller
.IP "pctldesc" 12
descriptor for this pin controller
.IP "driver_data" 12
private pin controller data for this pin controller
.IP "pctldev" 12
pin controller device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns zero on success or an error number on failure.

The pinctrl device will be automatically released when the device is unbound.
